    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While ear drops can be useful for earwax removal, the situation you’re describing isn’t typical earwax blockage or a common \"pressure thing.\" A sudden pop with hearing loss could possibly indicate that the ear drum has been impacted, there is a perforation, or you're experiencing tinnitus or another complication. Utilizing ear drops without understanding the full picture can lead to potential worsening of the condition. It's often best practice to avoid using ear medications (like drops or solutions) at home unless you've received professional guidance specifically attending to your case. Even if you're pressed for time contemplating waiting, consider scheduling an urgent appointment with an otolaryngologist or an urgent care clinic, or contacting your primary care doctor to seek advice. They're equipped to give you preliminary advice over the phone and potentially arrange a quick examination if they believe it's necessary. Ignoring this could lead to prolonged discomfort or complications. Your health and the delicate structures of your ear are worth prioritizing, even amidst a busy work schedule.",
